      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt-free seasoning blend",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon",
      "notes": ""
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the coconut oil in a tagine or Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "Add the beef and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the red wine jelly, orange zest, and orange juice. Stir to combine.",
    "Add the thyme and bay leaves, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the salt-free seasoning blend, and stir to combine.",
    "Cover the tagine and transfer it to the oven. Cook for 2.5 hours, or until the beef is tender.",
    "Remove the tagine from the oven and let it cool slightly.",
    "Serve the beef and sauce over rice or with some crusty bread.",
    "Discard the bay leaves and serve hot."
  ],
